com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.core.domain.refset

Class SnomedReferenceSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.b2international.snowowl.core.domain.BaseComponent
      • com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.core.domain.SnomedComponent
        • com.b2international.snowowl.snomed.core.domain.refset.SnomedReferenceSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IComponent, java.io.Serializable

    public final class SnomedReferenceSet
extends SnomedComponent
    Represents a SNOMED CT Reference Set.
    Reference sets returned by search requests are populated based on the expand parameters passed into the BaseResourceRequestBuilder#setExpand(String) methods. The expand parameters can be nested allowing a fine control for the details returned in the resultset. The supported expand parameters are:

    • members() - returns the members of this reference set as part of the reference set
    The number of expanded fields can be controlled with the limit: directive. For example: members(limit:Integer.MAX_VALUE)

    Expand parameters can be nested to further expand or filter the details returned.

    Since:
    4.5
    See Also:
    SnomedConcept, SnomedDescription, SnomedRelationship, SnomedReferenceSetMember, Serialized Form
